The paper proposes a novel convolutional neural network (CNN) for the diagnosis of Alzheimer's Disease (AD) using multi-modality imaging data. The paper focuses on image classification and deep learning, which are the main topics of the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of artificial intelligence (AI) algorithms for AD diagnosis also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of 3D image-processing CNNs, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-modality imaging data, which is relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
